[http://www.ruckuswireless.com/products/zoneflex-indoor/7321 Product page] The '''Ruckus Wireless''' logo, "SPANIEL", and "(C)2012 Ruckus Wireless Inc." is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :"100-11215-001 REV A" is silkscreened on one of the antennas. The Flash chip appears to be a S25FL256S (FL256SAIFK0??). [http://www.smallnetbuilder.com/wireless/wireless-news/31751-ruckus-wireless-announces-high-and-low-end-aps Ruckus Wireless Announces High and Low End APs - SmallNetBuilder] The FCC Quick Setup Guide specifies the default SSID(s) as '''WirelessX''' (where '''X''' is 1 through 8).
